item.title: Chthonophagia
item.description:
\Chthon`o*pha"gi*a\, Chthonophagy \Chtho*noph"a*gy\, n. [NL. chthonophagia; Gr. ?, ?, earth + ? to eat.]

A disease characterized by an irresistible desire to eat earth, observed in some parts of the southern United States, the West Indies, etc.

Webster’s Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913)

item.title: Coracoid
item.description:
\Cor"a*coid\, a.[Gr. ?; ko`rax crow + e’i^dos form.]

  1. Shaped like a crow’s beak.

  2. (Anat.) Pertaining to a bone of the shoulder girdle in most birds, reptiles, and amphibians, which is reduced to a process of the scapula in most mammals.

Webster’s Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913)
